being bright at an early age does not necessarily bring success upon growing up (proverb)

sentences.english: But the time may not be ripe.
sentences.chinese: 但是時機可能未必成熟。
因爲這個答案未必正確。

sentences.english: PUGILISTS and aesthetes are not necessarily in opposing corners.
sentences.chinese: 拳擊家和美學家未必就湊不到一塊兒。

sentences.english: Mentioned here is very broad, it may not correct.
sentences.chinese: 這裏講的是非常粗線條的，也未必正確。

sentences.english: But while the snub shape may be attractive, it is not necessary a blessing.
sentences.chinese: 儘管翹鼻子可能有魅力，但這未必是福。

sentences.english: In addition, with Gio arts Chiellini may not be able to play.
sentences.chinese: 除此之外，基耶利尼同吉奧文科也未必能夠出場。

sentences.english: It was unlikely that we should become confidants while Rogers was in retirement .
sentences.chinese: 在羅傑斯退職後，我們就未必能成爲知己。

sentences.english: Culture and refinement are not always concomitants of wealth.
sentences.chinese: 有財富未必就能有文雅氣質。

sentences.english: Filthy rich people are not not necessarily good-respected unless you possess noble characters.
sentences.chinese: 有錢人未必受人尊敬，除非有高尚的品格。

sentences.english: All that glitters is not gold.
sentences.chinese: 閃閃發光者未必都是金。

sentences.english: Simple machines can be efficient, but complex adaptive machinery cannot be.
sentences.chinese: 簡單機器可達成高效率，適合複雜型的機器則未必。

sentences.english: Even those with enough money to buy their own homes are not necessarily fortunate.
sentences.chinese: 即使那些買的起房的人也未必是幸運的。

sentences.english: This is not necessarily what we want.
sentences.chinese: 這樣的情況未必是我們想要的。

sentences.english: But Jingdong Mall is unlikely to look to list elsewhere.
sentences.chinese: 但是京東商城未必會尋找別處上市。

sentences.english: The man who achieved this influence was an unlikely candidate for such eminence.
sentences.chinese: 有這麼大影響的人，未必一定會獲得鼎鼎大名。

sentences.english: But where oolitic banks are well developed, there may not necessarily exist good reservoirs.
sentences.chinese: 但有鮞粒灘發育，未必就有儲層發育。
